# What each function does

---

## 1. Find node by id

```javascript
function getNode(id) {
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}
```

---

## 2. Physics update for nodes

```javascript
function updateNodes() {
  // pairwise repulsion between all nodes
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      const dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      const dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
      const force = config.repulsion / (dist * dist);

      const fx = dx / dist * force;
      const fy = dy / dist * force;

      nodes[i].vx += fx;
      nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx;
      nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }

  // spring forces along links
  for (let i = 0; i < links.length; i++) {
    const n1 = getNode(links[i].a);
    const n2 = getNode(links[i].b);
    if (!n1 || !n2) continue;

    const dx = n2.x - n1.x;
    const dy = n2.y - n1.y;
    const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
    const stretch = dist - links[i].rest;
    const force = (links[i].k || config.springForce) * stretch;

    n1.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
    n1.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    n2.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
    n2.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }

  // damping + pull toward screen center + integrate position
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    nodes[i].vx *= config.damping;
    nodes[i].vy *= config.damping;

    nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.centance;
    nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.centance;

    nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
    nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
  }
}
```

### Meaning
This is classic simple particle physics:

- **repulsion** keeps nodes from collapsing together
- **springs** keep linked nodes near desired distances
- **damping** prevents perpetual acceleration
- **center attraction** keeps the whole layout from drifting away

This creates a gently moving graph-like cluster.

---

## 3. Spawn a particle

```javascript
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= config.particles) return;

  const node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  const angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  const speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * ROOT2_2;

  particles.push({
    x: node.x,
    y: node.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + (Math.random() * PHI * ROOT2_2)
  });
}
```

### Meaning
Every few ticks it emits a small drifting particle from a random node.

---

## 4. Update particles

```javascript
function updateParticles() {
  for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    const p = particles[i];

    p.vx *= (1 - config.attenuation * 0.125);
    p.vy *= (1 - config.attenuation * 0.125);

    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;
    p.age++;

    if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
      particles.splice(i, 1);
    }
  }
}
```

### Meaning
Particles gradually slow down and disappear after a while.

---

## 5. Smooth camera/phase toward target

```javascript
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x += (target.x - camera.x) * config.phase;
  camera.y += (target.y - camera.y) * config.phase;
  camera.phase += (target.phase - camera.phase) * config.phase;
}
```

### Meaning
Simple interpolation / easing.

Again, since `target` never changes in this snippet, this doesn’t do much.

---

## 6. Main loop

```javascript
function tickFrame() {
  updateNodes();
  updateParticles();
  updateCamera();

  if (tick % 3 === 0) {
    spawnParticle();
  }

  tick++;
}

setInterval(tickFrame, 16);
```

### Meaning
Runs the simulation at roughly 60 Hz.

